      A collection of the best open data sets and open-source tools for data science, wrapped in an easy-to-use REST/JSON API with [command line](http://www.datasciencetoolkit.org/developerdocs#commandline), [Python](http://www.datasciencetoolkit.org/developerdocs#python) and [Javascript](http://www.datasciencetoolkit.org/developerdocs#javascript) interfaces. Available as a [self-contained Vagrant VM](http://www.datasciencetoolkit.org/developerdocs#vagrant) or [EC2 AMI](http://www.datasciencetoolkit.org/developerdocs#amazon) that you can deploy yourself.
      
      It's essentially a specialized Linux distribution, with a lot of useful data software pre-installed and exposing a simple interface. For full documentation, see [http://www.datasciencetoolkit.org/developerdocs](http://www.datasciencetoolkit.org/developerdocs).
      
